</para>
    <para id="id8959124">g/ Plotting the DTFT</para>
    <para id="id6180126">Because the DTFT of a real DT function</para>
    <para id="id8706928">has a period of 1,</para>
    <para id="id9119137">has conjugate symmetry (real part and magnitude of the DTFT are even functions of φ, the imaginary part and angle are odd functions of φ), </para>
    <para id="id7601806">the DTFT need only be plotted over the frequency range 0 ≤ φ ≤ 0.5. Nevertheless, we shall plot several DTFTs over a larger range of φ to reinforce the periodicity and symmetry properties.</para>
    <para id="id9557382">III. DT FOURIER TRANSFORM PAIRS</para>
