    <para id="id4147630">A single unit sample has a DTFT that is 1. Addition of a pair of unit samples at ±1 adds a cosine wave of frequency 1 to the DTFT. Addition of a pair of unit samples at ±2 adds a cosine of frequency 2 to the DTFT. As more unit samples are added, x[n] → 1 and the DTFT approaches a periodic impulse train of frequency 1.</para>
